Historian Stephen Chambers has collected more than 100 rare photographs of the doomed Gallipoli landings which claimed 140,000 lives in eight months of fighting .
They include poignant images of soldiers hosed down on the deck of the SS Bulwark in Turkey's Dardanelles straits .
An estimated 1,000 Allied soldiers died on the first day of the disastrous invasion until the evacuation of the city of Constantinople with no material gain .